I work in the neighborhood and just discovered Little Purity. I love this place - classic Brooklyn diner with great food and especially excellent service. And I mean that - there is usually just two people up front and they are always working so hard and have a great attitude (sorry I haven't asked names, you're both great!). They've also gone above and beyond with Covid-measures. Eat here, be nice and tip them well!

We found Little Purity through seeking a place for breakfast near our hotel in Brooklyn. It is a small diner just like one would picture a family owned neighborhood establishment. They had all the expected breakfast items with a few tweaks that recognized the multi-cultural nature of New York's boroughs. For example. I had Spanish sausage with my eggs.  The wait staff were very friendly and helpful. We walked there, so I am not sure what, if any, dedicated parking existed.

They have excellent milkshakes and the BLT I had was perfect, the bread was nice and crunchy as well as the bacon. The prices were also very reasonable, especially for the neighborhood.

Hands down the best diner in Park Slope,  maybe even the best in Brooklyn. Their food is off the charts delicious and the menu is what you would expect a local diner to have, plus some really spectacular burger choices for later in the day. The staff is extremely friendly and attentive, including the owner whose first priority is making sure the customers are happy. Little Purity is my regular neighborhood go to spot for weekend breakfast and weekday lunch.

A lovely discovery We live at the Flatbush end of Park Slope so this diner is not a drop in for us,  but we had an early morning  appointment in this area and stopped here for breakfast: what a delightful place. The wait staff was  lovely, sweet, appropriately attentive. The vibe very welcoming and homey. I hesitate to be overly effusive given this was our first time and we didn't dive into the many offerings. I will say the homemade strawberry jam was a real surprise and delicious. I loved the mismatched Fiesta Ware cups and saucers. Small touches like that told me they have a sense of pride in their service and quality. We will definitely go back. It appears to be a favorite among locals.

That Saturday morning, the kitchen seemed to be busy because our food took 20+ minutes to be served, but another couple, who seemed to be friends with all the staff, and they got their later than we did, they got served in less than 10 minutes (and one of them ordered the same thing I ordered)....
